2:T423,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"How Much Electricity Does an Automated Gate Actually Use?","description":"Worried about energy bills? Discover the true running costs of electric gates in London, including standby electricity, servicing, and repairs.","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/guides/electric-gate-running-costs/","datePublished":"2026-01-17","dateModified":"2026-01-17","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/images/gates/gate-automation-intercom-evening-lighting.png","width":1200,"height":630},"author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Driveway Gates London","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Driveway Gates London","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/android-chrome-512x512.png","width":512,"height":512}},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/guides/electric-gate-running-costs/"}}3:T639,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How much electricity does an electric gate use per year?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A modern 24V residential gate motor uses approximately 60 to 70 kWh per year for a typical London household with around 10 gate cycles per day. At current UK electricity rates of around 24p per kWh, this works out to roughly £15 to £17 per year — well under £2 per month."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does leaving the gate on standby use a lot of electricity?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. A modern gate motor in standby draws only 3 to 8 watts — comparable to a low-energy LED bulb. Even on standby continuously for a year, the cost would be under £10 at current electricity rates."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How often should electric gates be serviced?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Once per year for residential systems. A standard annual service covers motor lubrication, safety sensor testing, hinge adjustment, intercom checks, and battery backup verification. It typically takes an hour and costs £120 to £200 in London."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is it worth upgrading from an old 230V gate motor to a new 24V system?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Usually yes, if the existing gate structure is sound. Modern 24V motors are more efficient, quieter, smoother, and more reliable. The upgrade typically costs £800 to £1,800 depending on gate type, and the energy and repair savings often recover this within 5 to 7 years."}}]}6:["slug","electric-gate-running-costs","d"]
